<TITLE> 2 die in road crash </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Chittagong, May 17 (bdnews24.com)  Two persons were killed and two others injured as a bus and a CNG-run auto rickshaw collided head-on on the Chittagong-Cox's Bazar Highway in Patia. One of the dead was identified as M Faruk, 45, the auto rickshaw driver. The injured Azizul Islam, 18, and Ferdous, 42, were taken to Chittagong Medical College Hospital. Patia police chief Imtiaz Ahmed said the Chittagong-bound bus of Borak Paribahan crashed into the auto rickshaw at around 9:30am. The auto rickshaw driver died on the way to hospital, he said. Police seized the bus but its driver managed to get away. 
